&lt;b&gt;Features&lt;/b&gt;
- seven predefined scrollbar colors + customizeable colors
- two scrollbar widths (13px and 17px)
- two scrollbar backgrounds (light and dark)
- English/German options window
- works with Firefox and Thunderbird
- colorpicker to style custom scrollbars
- textfield to set background color (hexcode) for custom scrollbars
- option to pick a random scrollbar on startup
- option to hide scrollbars
- options to customize scrollbars background, thumb, buttons, size
- option to make scrollbars transparent (only if "GlassMyFox"-extension is used)  (Firefox only, AeroGlass Windows 7 / Vista only)

This add-on is highly recommended for people, who like to have "high contrast" scrollbars. Colorized scrollbars can be more kindly for eyes.

&lt;b&gt;"NewScrollbars" extension also works with some themes (depends on theme).&lt;/b&gt; 

&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/addon/hidescrollbars/" rel="nofollow"&gt;HideScrollbars&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;
A very small add-on to only remove scrollbars.

&lt;b&gt;Note&lt;/b&gt;: If a website is already open and scrollbar options are enabled/disabled (in the add-ons manager), every page has to be reloaded to make changes take effect (for any active, opened or loaded website).

&lt;b&gt;Important
The 'new' scrollbars are images. Images get altered using applications zoom feature. Go to "View"-&amp;gt;"Zoom" and hit the setting to only zoom text, so scrollbars size doesn't get changed on zooming.&lt;/b&gt; All scrollbar-styling add-ons and themes suffer from this problem and there is no workaround.

